description: Portland Trail Blazers head coach and basketball Hall of Famer Chauncey Billups, Miami Heat guard Terry Rozier and former NBA journeyman Damon Jones are among 34 people indicted in connection with two separate federal gambling investigations announced by the Eastern District of New York on Thursday. #CNN #News

author: CNN
description: Nevada’s Extraterrestrial Highway near Area 51 is known for UFO sightings. If you drive through it without being abducted by aliens, you can try to rest for the night at a famously haunted, clown-themed motel. author: CNN
description: CNN's Matt Wells discusses how the choice of music at a royal service at the Vatican Thursday was symbolic of England's religious history and noting the symbolism of King Charles III praying with Pope Leo centuries after King Henry VIII's break from the Catholic Church.

author: CNN
description: The US military has conducted deadly strikes in the Caribbean Sea and Pacific Ocean on suspected drug smugglers. At least 37 people in total have been killed in the known strikes, officials have said. Legal experts and lawmakers on both sides of the aisle have questioned the legality of the strikes. CNN’s David Culver traveled to Ecuador to track down a man who survived a boat strike. #cnn #news #shorts
title: Fisherman survives one of Trump’s strikes

author: CNN
description: Former special counsel Jack Smith is asking Congress and the DOJ to let him testify publicly, citing “many mischaracterizations” of his investigations that led to criminal charges against Donald Trump in 2023 over classified records and 2020 election-related actions, according to a letter sent Thursday to House and Senate Judiciary leaders. Former FBI Deputy Director, Andrew McCabe joins CNN's Kasie Hunt on The Arena.                              #CNN #News
title: Jack Smith seeks approval to testify publicly before Congress

description:

#cnn #news

description: Denise Blake is a US Department of Defense employee and says she hasn't bought groceries since the government shutdown on October 1st. title: This federal worker drove over an hour to a food bank that ran out of food

description: President Trump has repeatedly said that work on the ballroom is privately funded by himself and donors and will cost nothing to taxpayers. description:

CNN’s Christopher Lamb joins CNN's Christiane Amanpour to discuss.
#cnn   #News
title: King Charles prays with Pope Leo at the Vatican in a historic moment

author: CNN
description:
President Trump is escalating his war against "narcoterrorists,” Wednesday saying the U.S. military has the legal authority to strike alleged drug smugglers on land. The same day, Secretary of Defense Pete Hegseth announced an eighth lethal strike on a boat in international waters. Democratic Congresswoman Sara Jacobs says "this is murder" and her fellow Hill lawmakers on the NewsNight panel react.



 #CNN #News
title: 'This is murder': Dem Rep. reacts to Trump's boat strikes

author: CNN
description:
With New York City’s mayoral election fast approaching, one candidate in particular has managed to break through the noise. Zohran Mamdani, the Democratic Socialist-backed progressive whose campaign videos have gone viral, has become the face of a growing leftist wave. But is it a one-city phenomenon, or the beginning of something bigger? Audie talks to CNN contributor Astead Herndon. His story about Mamdani’s campaign was just published in the New York Times Magazine. He is now a host and Editorial Director at Vox.

Listen to the full episode of CNN's The Assignment podcast: http://swap.fm/l/tawacyt102325

#cnn #news #politics #democrats #mamdani #zorhan #zorhanmamdani #dsa #democraticsocialism
title: What Zohran Mamdani’s rise says about the future of the left | The Assignment

description: A daycare in Rockdale County, Georgia was set on fire. The arsonist, who was caught on camera, poured gasoline inside the building before setting it on fire and running away. No arrests have been made as investigators work to determine a motive. #cnn #georgia #arson
title: Arsonist caught on video setting fire to Georgia daycare

description: President Donald Trump has proceeded with enormous latitude as he constructs his massive new ballroom, bypassing concerns raised by preservationists and so far stopping short of seeking approval from the commission overseeing construction on federal buildings to tear down the entirety of the White House East Wing.
